Title: Coll. 170. Ms. 593. Page 112
Description.abstract: f. 54r-v, ruled but blank.Pseudo-Phalaris, Epistolae, translated from the Greek by Francesco Griffolini of Arezzo (1418-1483) with dedication to Domenico Novello Malatesta of Cesena (1418-1465); the final four letters are dedicated to King Alfonso I of Naples (1442-1458). 142 epistles falsely attributed to Phalaris, tyrant of Agrigento, s. VI BC; they were actually written by a sophist, s. II AD. Hain *12872-12906; earliest dated printing, Treviso and Paris 1471. The collection of letters in 170/593 closely resembles that in a Venice 1493-95 incunable (minus the edition's concluding dedicatory letter to Francesco Pellato). The list of manuscripts of the Epistolae in D. Muratore, Le Epistole di Falaride; Catalogo dei manoscritti (Rome, 2006) lists MSS containing the Epistolae, does not include 170/593. Marginal pointing hands, bracketing lines, and some underlining of text; contemporary annotations (ff. 19 and 27) in semi-cursive, cut off at the outer edge.
